wikipedia_page.main: Frederick William Sykes FRCO (1862 – 30 October 1932) was an organist and composer based in England.

response: The organ builders from John Compton had been working until 11.00 pm on Friday 19 October, and shortly after midnight on Saturday the organist Frederick William Sykes spotted flames coming from the organ chamber.Western Times, Monday 22 October 1906. p.4. Selby Abbey Entirely Destroyed by Fire on Saturday The organ builders had been installing a new kinetic gas engine to provide power to the new organ. Initial reports that the new organ equipment was to blame for the fire were later proved inaccurate.Sheffield Evening Telegraph. Friday 14 December 1906. p.5. The Selby Abbey Fire
